# Trivy ignore list — risk acceptance for the strict CVE gate in release.yml.
#
# All entries are CVEs in transitive Go-dependencies pulled in by the
# ProjectDiscovery `subfinder` binary baked into the backend image
# (built from source via the multi-stage Dockerfile). These are HIGH/CRITICAL
# against the *library*, but the vulnerable code paths are not exercised
# by subfinder's actual usage (passive subdomain enumeration: HTTPS GET
# requests to public APIs like crt.sh, hackertarget, alienvault, wayback).
#
# Revisit when:
#   - subfinder upstream updates go.mod to pull newer x/crypto + x/net
#   - or we move subfinder out of the backend image entirely (planned
#     under the Kali-attack-box arc — see project_kali_attack_box_arc memory).

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# golang.org/x/crypto/ssh — subfinder does not establish SSH connections,
# act as an SSH client, or run an SSH server. Vulnerable code paths are
# never reached.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-39827
CVE-2026-39828
CVE-2026-39829
CVE-2026-39830
CVE-2026-39831
CVE-2026-39832
CVE-2026-39835
CVE-2026-42508
CVE-2026-46595
CVE-2026-46597

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# golang.org/x/net/html — subfinder consumes structured JSON responses
# from passive-recon APIs, not arbitrary HTML.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-25680
CVE-2026-25681
CVE-2026-27136
CVE-2026-42502
CVE-2026-42506

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# golang.org/x/net (HTTP/2 + IDNA)
# CVE-2026-33814 is in net/http/internal/http2 server-side code — subfinder
#   is an HTTP/1.1+2 *client* only, never serves HTTP.
# CVE-2026-39821 is in IDNA; subfinder normalizes domain inputs already
#   validated against the engagement scope, so attacker-controlled IDNA
#   input doesn't reach the vulnerable path.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39821

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Go stdlib (os.Root symlink-following) — v1.33.1 addition.
# CVE-2026-39822 is in os.Root, added by Trivy DB update on 2026-07-14.
# subfinder builds with an older Go toolchain (v1.25.11 + v1.26.4) that
# still ships this bug. Subfinder never uses os.Root — it writes only its
# own stdout / stderr and reads no filesystem paths derived from
# attacker-controlled input. Vulnerable code path is not reached.
# Revisit alongside the other subfinder CVEs above once we move subfinder
# out of the backend image (Kali attack-box arc).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-39822

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# sharp (Next.js image optimizer) — v2.24.9 addition.
# GHSA-f88m-g3jw-g9cj bundles four libvips CVEs (CVE-2026-33327/33328/35590/
# 35591), all triggered by processing malicious image files. Frontend renders
# our own asset PNGs (Leaflet marker icons, Dossier tab thumbnails via
# freeipapi/ipinfo lat/lon → static Leaflet render) and analyst-uploaded
# screenshot attachments. Attachments already go through backend defusedxml
# + size-cap validation; frontend never processes attacker-supplied images
# from outside the tenant. Full fix pending sharp@^0.35 + npm lockfile
# regen (deferred — clean IPv6 needed for npm install).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GHSA-f88m-g3jw-g9cj
